# Worker Gate

This repository is a market-integrity monitoring prototype. Keep changes
reviewable and evidence-first.

## Required Design Gate

Before implementing a non-trivial change, create design notes under:

```text
docs/designs/<feature-name>/
```

Use these files when the change affects detector behavior, external data
collection, persistence/state, report semantics, GitHub Actions, or dashboard
outputs:

```text
01_ARCHITECTURE_MAP.md
02_DATA_FLOW.md
03_IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md
04_REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md
```

After creating design docs, commit them and stop for review unless the user has
explicitly asked to continue with implementation in the same task.

## Lightweight Exemptions

Design docs are not required for:

- Documentation-only edits
- Cursor rules, PR templates, or process docs
- Small config-only changes
- Test-only changes
- Tiny covered fixes that do not change detector thresholds or report semantics

## Review Standard

For surveillance-related behavior, use observed criteria and analyst-review
language. Do not present heuristic output as a conclusion about intent,
identity, ownership, or wrongdoing.
